annotation.TEXT: Aha!
Last time, on Something else... I clipped through this cannon head here in Bullet Bird Boom, and I forgot to include the slowed-down instant replays of this in the previous episode, so here you go!
Alright, let's get ready to ruuumbleee!!!
This tower, it just keeps going up...
To be continued...
It's this one! Ha, the Dry Bones on the left is getting cooked... Except, since sprite buoyancy apparently isn't turned on here, he's not really burning up, and can still throw bones.
BGM: Wario Land (GB) - Syrup Castle Map
Whoa, that was close! I wasn't expecting that firebar to move like a pendulum!
What is that? Oh, it's like a Rip Van Fish, but there's no water for it to swim in. Also, I can stomp these guys, apparently. That's cool.
Oh, what? There was no coin indicating the presence of that one! (But honestly, it showed itself a few seconds beforehand, so I should've been paying attention.)
Hey there, goofy-looking Hammer Duder.
Oh, man. The moon doesn't have a level name. Is it actually a transition to a whole new world?
I almost got sandwiched by those Li'l Sparkies.
Going up!
Oh, finally! So, is it final boss time now?
Oh, man. The music changed. I must be approaching the final boss battle.
That was a tight squeeze.
Looks like it's following the Roy's Castle pattern, which makes sense, since this level's on the main overworld and not on a submap.
Yo, RVFW... BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! TRI-FORMATION! WOO!
Zwee! Halfway done with The Last Castle already, eh?
Gotta be patient here. Rushing will only get you burned.
Man, how much longer is this level? This second half has lasted longer than the first half already.
And now for the mace-dodging event.
Yeah, I think the peach will probably be helpful here, and I'll let this guy smack me on purpose once just to give him some self-esteem, or something.
MOOOOOONNN!!!
It looked like I could've duck-jumped over that wall, but why risk it?
There's no reset door either, so would players be permanently stuck (well, until time runs out) if they lost their peach here?
There's definitely something more up there, but the screen's not scrolling up...
Okay, so I assume all that's up there was that bunch of coins that I just collected, right?
Well, there's a power up there, which I don't need right now.
Wait... Oh, doy. You can climb these chains, so of course a peach isn't actually required just to proceed here. (That was a brief brain fart I just had there.)
Oh, man. It's one of those Pompon Flowers from Super Mario Land. Unfortunately, I can't attack it since it's surrounded by solid walls, but it can certainly attack me.
Man, the peach is so good here.
There were four coins over there for whatever reason. (If I missed a secret there, or anywhere around here, let me know.)
Bonk! Good thing we're on the main overworld and not on a submap, or else he'd be tossing hammers more rapidly.
Gotta watch out for Podoboos coming from both above and below. Fortunately, the coins seem to indicate where they are.
Yep, it's a block snake.
Oh, I'm not giving up now. I totally think I can assault your spacial fortress alone.
What? I just get a pipe that transitions straight to a "Course Clear!" screen without having a chance to hit a goal tape for bonus stars? What a gyp!
Ah, end of the line.
...Wait, what? Not ready? You got me (and probably everybody else) all hyped up, and you're not ready yet?! Come on, man!
But, there's no point in me wasting time with that, seeing how I've already got 99 lives.
Oh, man! It's The Evil Guy!
Oh, man. There's a life-farming spot here!
Some of the coin sound effects sound unusually loud for some reason.
So, will this level end with a goalpost, so that I can play one more bonus game?
Huh, would it not be possible to advance from here without a peach?
No, not quite yet. Hmm... Do I want this?
"Tick." (Graze +1)
Whoa, wasn't expecting a fireball-shooting statue to appear there.
Huh. Did I just get a couple coins up there?
Should "I'm out" be changed to something like "I'm outta here"?
Oh, yep. It's totally another world (with moon graphics taken from SML2's Space Zone)! So, this hack isn't quite done yet, folks!
Wait, did you say... THE MOOOOOONNN!?!?!?
Whoa! I didn't realize those RVFWs could move so fast!
Yeah, that could've gone badly, but it didn't, so that's good... Whoa, that 1-up sound effect was loud. The sound effects are probably clashing with certain parts of the music at times.
Uh, oh. That looks like a block snake...

Awesome, I can now burninate stuff again, including these Rip Van Fish Wannabes. (Let's call them RVFWs from now on... Or at least until the end of this episode, since I'm sure someone will tell me what they're actually called and the game they're from.)
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! It is now time to take on The Last Castle!
Ha. Scrollin' away the bone.
Yeah, I'm totally glad I decided to take the fire flower!
Alright, am I finally done with this level now?
BGM: Bowser Strikes Back - Kamek's Tower by Jimmy52905
Huh. I was expecting there to be a power up in one of those blocks for some reason. (Not that I need any power ups right now.)
Is this more fun than a barrel of Dry Bones?
Whoa, there's a second midpoint in this place? That's a first for this hack. Alright, here's the boss door. Are you ready guys? I know I am... for final boss time!
Alright, here we go!
Alright, so next time, I guess I'll be starting with this Switch Room level on the moon's chin!
So, can I climb over this wall and skip the whole level? ...Nah, it's not gonna be that easy, you silly... Although, that might've been a good place to hide some goodies.
Is it... boss time?
There's a double firebar pendulum. Gotta move through at just the right time.
Yeah, I have a feeling that fireballs would be more useful here.
Hmm... One of these pits is not like the others. Can you tell which one?
